Is there an easier way, in Axiom, of drawing two curves on the same set of
axes than with the getGraph, putGraph and makeViewport2D commands?  It would
be nice (for me!) simply to be able to enter, say

draw([sin(x),x-x^3/6],x=-2*%pi..2*%pi)

and have the graphs of both functions in the list drawn on the same axes.
But Axiom doesn't seem to support this syntax.

Thanks,
Alasdair

